Try asking your advisor and see if they know anything or have any suggestions. Professors might have large inboxes so it could take a while.

Have you contact the professor and CS advising to clarify? If "not allowed" mean that you won't get credit for taking both CS186 and Data Engineering CS 194, then taking it might not count towards the major anyway.

I'm not sure if you'll get credit or not, but I'd strongly recommend not doing Data Engineering after CS 186 since you won't end up getting much out of the class. The idea behind the requirement that you shouldn't is that theres substantial overlap in the courses, and your resources would be better spent elsewhere given that you're paying through your nose to take classes (both directly and opportunity cost wise). 

You mention that you can't get into any other CS classes - have you tried EE classes? Additionally you might not get credit for it, so there's no benefit to take it.
I'm having the same circumstance here. Did you get any updates on this?
